＆スーパームーン&スタージョンムーンです！
🌝ブルームーン（Blue Moon）は、天文季節の４つの満月のうちの３つ目（季節のブルームーン）または暦月の２つ目の満月（暦のブルームーン）のことです。
🌝1年で最も月が大きく見える「#スーパームーン 」！スーパームーンとは、月が地球に最も近づく軌道上のポイントで満月になる現象を指します。
スーパームーンの満月は通常の満月より7%大きく、16%明るく見えます。
🌝8月の満月を「#スタージェンムーン
（#Sturgeon_Moon ／#チョウザメ月 ）」と呼ばれています🦈スタージョンムーンは、「自由」「個性」「自立」「友情」「平和」「オリジナリティ」「ネットワーク」などをキーワードとしており、これらにまつわる願い事が叶うとされています。

天気が良くなかったですが、夜中に雲の切れて綺麗な月🌝が見れました😆

Occultation • 21-08-2024

The weather forecast was bad, clouds everywhere, but I had faith. I had many problems because of this, the exposure and gain of Saturn and the Moon are very different and if we add the clouds to the formula… 😅

This is not the best composite you will see in the social media, but for me it is more natural. Saturn is taken from the video where it is occulting and the photo of the moon was taken 30 min before.

But the best of this was to see it and capture it live 🤩

I hope you like it! ❤️

Moon” The night before and night of a full moon are my chances every month to capture this amazing event to share with you all. Unfortunately here in Connecticut and much of New England rain & clouds decided to crash the party during moonrise. Last night I went down by the shore in neighboring Madison, CT to see if the clouds would clear in time, but during moonrise it was a wild storm complete with a downpour and lightning. I was actually able to see the moon glowing slightly through my windshield during this for less than a minute before disappearing again in the dark storm clouds. After the heavy rain passed Mother Nature’s fireworks continued and I instead focused on capturing them with my phone camera. I may actually post a cool image I was able to pull from this and share so keep an eye out. Since I didn’t capture the moon I wanted to share this image of a previous August’s Super Blue Moon in my hometown of Guilford, CT. I have to mention how ridiculous it is to see the posts showing an actual blue colored moon when promoting this “blue moon” every year as it has nothing to do with its color and another ridiculous editing display by many. When it showed up in between thick clouds it was a shade of orange like it always is when it is rising above the horizon. As I got higher up the color faded into its more usual brighter self as it slipped perfectly in between the clouds. I love how the clouds around the moon provide extra elements and drama to the scene instead of just having the moon sitting solo in a clear sky. Like most of my moonscape images this was captured using my Canon R5 body + Canon RF 100-500mm lens (@500mm) which has become my go to rig. Also for any other photographers that ask for settings: ISO 1600, f7.1, 1/125 sec.

Pessoas de diferentes países veem a Lua de diferentes formas ao mesmo tempo...

A diferença na forma como a Lua é vista entre o Hemisfério Norte e o Hemisfério Sul acontece devido à curvatura da Terra. Como a Terra é esférica, a orientação de quem observa a Lua varia conforme a posição geográfica.

No Hemisfério Norte, os observadores veem a Lua de uma forma, enquanto no Hemisfério Sul, a mesma Lua parece estar de cabeça para baixo em relação ao que é visto no Norte. Isso ocorre porque, ao mudar de hemisfério, você está basicamente "invertendo" seu ponto de vista em relação ao espaço. É como se você estivesse olhando a Lua de "ponta-cabeça" em comparação com uma pessoa do outro hemisfério.

Esse fenômeno também pode ser observado ao viajar entre hemisférios; as constelações e outros corpos celestes também mudam de orientação. Mas mesmo assim, é a mesma Lua, só que vista de ângulos diferentes!
